Package controller

Class AddAppointment

  • java.lang.Object
    • controller.AddAppointment
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javafx.fxml.Initializable
    public class AddAppointment
extends java.lang.Object
implements javafx.fxml.Initializable
    Controller class for AddAppointment.fxml.

    Initializes the view with a table showing all appointments currently in the database and with fields for the user to input information for a new appointment.

    Handles input validation and facilitates adding an appointment to the database.

    See Also:
    AppointmentsManager

      • onAddClick

        public void onAddClick​(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
                throws java.io.IOException
        AddAppointment onAction class method.

        Adds an appointment to the database.

        Validates user input and checks for rule violations. Violations include: scheduling an appointment that overlaps with an existing appointment for a given customer, scheduling an appointment outside of the office hours (8:00AM to 10:00PM EST), and scheduling an appointment on the weekend.

        Parameters:
        actionEvent - onAction event tied to clicking the 'add' button
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - catch IO issues navigating to dashboard

      • initialize

        public void initialize​(java.net.URL url,
                       java.util.ResourceBundle resourceBundle)
        Overrides the implementation of the Initializable interface. On class instantiation: populates the schedule table with Appointments from the database, populates the ComboBoxes (Contact, Customer, User) from the database, and sets start/end time ComboBox values.
